==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mercurialize
<hw>Mer*cu"ri*al*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Mercurialized</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Mercurializing</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>To affect
with mercury.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Photography)</fld> <def>To treat with mercury; to
expose to the vapor of mercury.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mercurialize</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mercurialize
<hw>Mer*cu"ri*al*ize</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To be sprightly,
fantastic, or capricious.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mercurially</ent>⟦br⟧
